    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Government spending transparent, adjust funding \"increases\" for inflation",
        "additional_details": "Full Fact provides evidence that the Grant review for police funding amounts to a cut after inflation.\r\nhttps://fullfact.org/crime/police-funding-england-and-wales/\r\n\r\nConservatives say Labour voted against an increase.\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/conservatives/photos/a.288165009278.146725.8807334278/10155780194029279/?type=3&theater\r\n\r\nLabour say Conservatives voted for a real terms cut.\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/labourparty/posts/10155283147077411",
        "background": "Often funding increases are announced, which amount to a funding cut after inflation. The only transparent approach is to deflate figures for inflation to give an increase figure in \"real terms\".",
